# Markdown is excluded, deliberately and permanently.
#
# In this repo the prose IS the product — the ADR log, the mission outputs,
# and the constitution are what the workshop exhibits. It is hand-wrapped at
# ~76 columns and the formatting carries meaning. Two failures, both observed
# rather than hypothetical:
#
#   1. Prettier normalizes *emphasis* to _emphasis_ and there is no option to
#      change it. One save flipped CLAUDE.md against the 60 other files that
#      use asterisks.
#   2. It re-indents a continuation paragraph under a nested list item so the
#      paragraph binds to the wrong bullet. In CLAUDE.md that silently moved
#      "structural rules are linted by validate-workshop.ts" under the
#      settings-files bullet, changing which files the sentence claimed to
#      cover. A formatter quietly altering the meaning of the constitution is
#      not a trade worth making for consistent list indentation.
#
# docs/decisions/INDEX.md is generated by scripts/reindex-decisions.ts and is
# covered by the rule above; it is named separately so that narrowing *.md
# later cannot re-include it by accident.
*.md
docs/decisions/INDEX.md

# TypeScript in scripts/ is deliberately NOT ignored. Formatting code is what
# prettier is here for, and those files are the enforcement layer — consistent
# shape makes a diff to them easier to read, which is the point (ADR 0035).

node_modules/
.DS_Store
